section.section:
Each Board shall:
Submit to the Secretary an annual report on:
The needs of individuals who have a mental disorder; and
The extent to which its State facility meets these needs;
Advise the administrative head of the State facility on its goals, programs, physical plant, and policies;
Help in evaluating the degree to which these goals are achieved;
Review and make recommendations about the annual budget of the State facility;
Assume leadership in developing community understanding of the needs of those who have a mental disorder; and
Carry out any other responsibility that the administrative head of the State facility requests.
